Even though she could see nothing of his face, his ever-changing aura was mammoth, giving him a presence that was as startling as it was powerful.
"Words to live by," Brenna said with a laugh as she turned and raced up the stairs.
"Ow, ow, ow, ow, ow," he groaned as he surveyed their surroundings.
"You look like you've got your own stories, Mighty Afrodite."
